                        <p class="placename">
                Biesnitzer Grund
            </p>
                            <p class="subcamp_of">
                <strong>Subcamp of: </strong>
                Gross-Rosen
            </p>
                            <p class="municipality">
                <strong>Location:</strong>
                G&#195;rlitz, Germany<br />
                            </p>
                            <div>
                Located in G&#195;rlitz, Saxony, it initially served as a forced labor camp from May 1943 to January 1944.  Jews were again sent there in August 1944 when it became a Gross-Rosen subcamp.
            </div>
